        "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
        "body": "Thanks for filing @sk-! The rationale here was to specifically target static assets that don't change and in that case we struggled to find a compelling reason why you should cache for a week but not a month or more. And if not a month why isn't it at a year?\r\n\r\nI think my preference to capture the original intention behind the audit would be narrowing the scope to assets with hash or version-like components in their URL rather than to weaken the rule.",
