        "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
        "body": "Thanks @patrickhulce for the answer. Would you in that case consider having two thresholds, one for those assets with hash or version-id, and another lower threshold for the remaining assets.\r\n\r\nWould it make sense then to simplify the code to explicitly ask for a year, rather than having a threshold, plus the data to interpolate the probability of a cache hit?\r\n\r\nAlso, it'd be great if the page https://web.dev/uses-long-cache-ttl/ would be explicit about the suggested cache time.",
